Enter the name of the recipe: Chocolate Cake

Name: Chocolate Cake
Ingredients:
- 2 cups all-purpose flour
- 2 cups granulated sugar
- 3/4 cup unsweetened cocoa powder
- 2 tsp baking powder
- 1 1/2 tsp baking soda
- 1 tsp salt
- 1 tsp instant coffee powder
- 1 cup buttermilk
- 1/2 cup vegetable oil
- 2 large eggs
- 2 tsp vanilla extract
- 1 cup boiling water
Steps:
- Preheat the oven to 350°F. Grease and flour two 9-inch round cake pans.
- In a large mixing bowl, whisk together the flour, sugar, cocoa powder, baking powder, baking soda, salt, and instant coffee powder.
- Add the buttermilk, vegetable oil, eggs, and vanilla extract. Beat with an electric mixer on low speed until just combined.
- Gradually pour in the boiling water and mix until smooth.
- Divide the batter evenly between the prepared cake pans.
- Bake for 30-35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cakes comes out clean.
- Cool the cakes in the pans for 10 minutes before removing them to wire racks to cool completely.

